data.text:
Independence National Historical Park, PA, USA

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 39.949532, -75.149879.

Independence National Historical Park, known as America's most historic square mile, is a huge historical site in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, United States, located at the heart of the city. It is home to numerous historical landmarks, museums, old buildings, and other points of interest, such as Independence Hall, Liberty Bell, Congress Hall, Signer's Garden, Liberty Bell Center, President's House Site, Carpenters' Hall, Merchant Exchange Building, the Museum of the American Revolution, National Constitution Center, Christ Church Burial Ground, Benjamin Franklin Grave, Benjamin Franklin Museum, Washington Square, Tomb of the Unknown Soldier, Independence Square, and many more. The park is accessible by 5th St Independence Hall Station and has a visitor center, Independence Visitor Center. Independence National Historical Park was designated as a U.S. National Historic Landmark District on October 15, 1966, and has been a U.S. National Historical Park since 1948.
